Bugs Remaining for TestFlight

Must Fix (blocking)

  Brush opacity slider REMOVED for v1.0 — root cause is architectural,
    not a one-line fix. Brush strokes are stamp-based (default spacing
    0.1 of brush size = ~10 stamps per brush diameter), and any per-
    stamp alpha multiplier accumulates acrosHis overlapping stamps, so
    the slider behaves like flow not opacity. Two attempts on Apr 27
    failed to ship: a scratch-buffer commit path softlocked features
    on iPad (likely the +64 MB allocation + sequential
    waitUntilCompleted calls), and a max-blend pipeline capped alpha
    correctly but RGB still accumulated to full color (max on alpha
    alone leaves RGB > alpha, so the pixel renders as over-bright).
    Both reverts are clean. UI removed: no Opacity section in
    BrushSettingsView. brushSettings.opacity stays at 1.0 internally.
    Real fix in v1.x = wet-ink preview path + scratch-buffer commit
    that produce identical premultiplied output (RGB and alpha both
    scaled by slider opacity), AND allow cross-stroke darkening.

  Paint bucket white outline + slow flood — premultiplied-alpha halo
    around the fill plus an unbounded CPU-side BFS flood fill. Halo
    was partially fixed Apr 15 (compositor now uses .one for source
    RGB since textures store premultiplied), still visible on device.
    A bounded BFS or a GPU compute kernel pass would help.

  ~~Move tool UX~~ — addressed Apr 27 alongside the perf rewrite (see
    "Move/rect/lasso drag was unusably slow" in Investigations
    Reference). No more full-doc extract on touchesBegan, no marquee,
    drag from any tap. Needs iPad retest.

  Export to Photos — MISSING. Single toolbar/gallery button: composite
    visible layers (use CanvasRenderer.compositeLayersToImage, already
    extracted via compositeLayersToTexture as of Apr 27) and call
    UIImageWriteToSavedPhotosAlbum. No App Store approval beyond the
